íŔ@ace0ac579c6e17abce453cbfeaa0824937e31c7dbb1ec471f6cb0785ffac89a5ŕ|Title: title: decode base32
Path: Examples
Content:
Decode arbitrary binary data
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> "AEBAGBAF" | decode base32
Length: 5 (0x5) bytes | null_char printable whitespace ascii_other non_ascii
00000000:   01 02 03 04  05                                      ‚ÄĘ‚ÄĘ‚ÄĘ‚ÄĘ‚ÄĘ


```
Decode an encoded string
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> "NBUQ====" | decode base32 | decode


```
Parse a string without padding
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> "NBUQ" | decode base32 --nopad
Length: 2 (0x2) bytes | null_char printable whitespace ascii_other non_ascii
00000000:   68 69                                                hi


```
íŔ@86b46b87657c0f766fc0897f7fd9d476905aeddaf22786e8caeae37938437cafŔĖTitle: title: decode base32
Path: Notes
Content:
The default alphabet is taken from RFC 4648, section 6.
Note this command will collect stream input.
